00000000000,"noxMt":0.000000000000000000,"nox":0.000000000000000000,"euEtsDetails":null},{"portName":"Taicang","displayOrder":4,"co2":231.765599999999980000,"eeoi":11.018680338577570000,"aer":null,"soxMt":1.825600000000000100,"sox":0.086793306798365300,"noxMt":7.300000000000001000,"nox":0.347059125563139100,"euEtsDetails":null}]},"remarkList":[{"modifiedDate":"2022-09-07T07:58:57.66","modifiedByFull":"Eden, Peter","remark":"Have today removed 2 bunker hedges for -$22,458.75 and -$43,672.50 respectively as these where un-allocated. this has s negative impact on PnL USD 66,131 / TCE 1,421 If this turns out to be incorrect we can add the hedges again. For now they are removed while running accruals in VMS"},{"modifiedDate":"2022-08-16T16:24:41.46","modifiedByFull":"Eisemann, Jason","remark":"Please find below intermediate calculation for FPMC 34 (Methanol)\nIntermediate Link\n\u2022\tPre-calc:               $15,116 x 51.2 days = ($502,955)\n\n\u2022\tEarnings:              $21,488 x 46.5 days = ($160,424)\nDifference:  We took delivery of her at Point Lisas to accommodate our 6th Proman methanol lifting to F\u2019East.  Maintenance of the Panama Canal was scheduled for July so even before we took delivery, the decision was made to pre-book about 25days out as all transit spots were filling up fast.  Unfortunately, delays in Houston, on her prior voyage forced us to cancel our booking slot.  To account for this, we included an addition 40K in port cost for Panama and 7 days waiting in the generation.   As luck would have it, we won a 3rd period slot and only incurred 1 day waiting, thus saving 7-10 days waiting (delays lengthened) for a natural transit.  Additionally, we saved 2.7 days on the laden passage and consumed on avg 4.5mt less per day as compared to S\u0026C in vessel register (24.2mt/day vs 19.9mt/day at 13kts).  Days in port extended by 2.6 as well but only could claim 0.6 days on demurrage.  Additionally, we had $198k positive bunker hedge as compared to estimated $160k."},{"modifiedDate":"2022-08-15T19:40:15.62","modifiedByFull":"Eisemann, Jason","remark":"Actual demurrage in put"},{"modifiedDate":"2022-08-09T21:34:47.56","modifiedByFull":"Eisemann, Jason","remark":"estimated demurrage in put"},{"modifiedDate":"2022-08-08T20:19:09.107","modifiedByFull":"Eisemann, Jason","remark":"TCE increase due to better than expected bunkers on ocean transit and less days"},{"modifiedDate":"2022-07-12T00:23:32.573","modifiedByFull":"Eisemann, Jason","remark":"difference is accounted for in winning 3rd period transit at P.Canal - Saves 6 days"}],"offhireList":[{"id":191784,"dateStartUtc":null,"dateEndUtc":null,"days":null,"displayOrder":0,"offhireReason":null,"remark":null,"offhireBunkerList":[{"id":84952,"gradeName":"LSBF","quantity":null,"price":null,"displayOrder":0}]}],"tcNumber":null,"tcOutIdEncrypted":null,"tcReletDetail":null}